Written: following personal final  Michael L. McBride. Beatitudes: Jesus lifted eyes disciples said "Blessed poor: kingdom God. Blessed ye hunger now: ye shall filled. Blessed ye weep now: ye shall laugh. Blessed ye men shall hate you shall separate company shall reproach you cast name evil Son Man's sake. Rejoice ye day leap joy: behold reward great Heaven: like manner fathers unto prophets. woe unto rich! ye received consolation. Woe unto full! ye shall hunger. Woe unto laugh now! ye shall moan weep. Woe unto you men shall speak well you! fathers false prophets. supremacy love gifts: Corinthians Chapter 13: 4-8: Love patient love kind jealous love brag arrogant act unbecoming; seek own provoked take account wrong suffered rejoice unrighteousness rejoices truth; bears things believes things hopes things endures things. Love never fails; gifts prophecy done away; tongues cease. abide faith hope love three: greatest love. Poem: stand grave weep sleep. diamond glints snow sunlight ripened grain. gentle autumn rain. awaken morning's hush swift uplifting rush quiet birds circled flight soft stars shine night. stand grave cry there. die. Signed Michael L. McBride #903 May 11 2000 Huntsville Texas  Spoken: Thank you um anticipated would try memorize recite beatitudes New Testament less Luke's beatitudes say  chapter love 1st Corinthians chapter 13 ah pretty much knew would able memorize much. also poem went along anticipation able to um fulfill desire provided written  made available anybody wants it believe. correct? So uh wanted hear say apologize grief caused know including the ah witness now. long. soon realize appear falling asleep. would leave point. dead point. irreversible. God bless you. Thank you. ]
